<title>
Radiator Cooling Fan Assembly On-Vehicle Inspection
</title>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A1606009001">
<title>
Radiator Cooling Fan Operation
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect scan tool to DLC (1) with ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L1F005">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "NNNNN-00024">
SUZUKI scan tool (SUZUKI-SDT)
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60AA20006.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "67.502mm" ver = "01" gw = "159" gh = "175"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON” and clear DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1104004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Select the “Radiator Fan” function in “Active Test”. 
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check radiator cooling fan operation at low and high modes.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If any abnormality is found, check cooling fan control system. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1604002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<spec>
